The dependent and independent variables were coded as follows: at: 1 for action A and -1 for action B (first stage actions, see Fig. 2). at-j: 0.5 if the first state action j trials back was A and -0.5 otherwise. rt-j: 0.5 if j trials back was rewarded and -0.5 otherwise. tt-j: 0.5 if j trials back transition was common and -0.5 if it was rare. Overall, the model includes (1 + j x 7) free parameters 

θLR={ β0,βaj,βrj,βtj,βa×rj,βa×tj,βr×tj,βa×r×tj }

.
